2 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 1-109, is
3 amended to read as follows:
4 Section 1-109. A. For all public schools in Oklahoma this
5 state, school shall actually be in session and classroom instruction
6 offered:
7 1. For not less than one hundred eighty (180) days; or
8 2. For not less than one thousand eighty (1,080) hours each
9 school year, if a district board of education adopts a school-hours
10 policy and notifies the State Board of Education prior to October 15
11 of the applicable school year; or
12 3. Beginning with the 2021-2022 school year, for not less than
13 one thousand eighty (1,080) hours with a minimum of one hundred
14 sixty-five (165) days of instruction each school year, if a district
15 board of education adopts a school-hours policy and notifies the
16 State Board of Education prior to October 15 of the applicable
17 school year; or
18 4. Beginning with the 2021-2022 school year, for not less than
19 one thousand eighty (1,080) hours each school year, if a district
20 board of education adopts a school-hours policy, notifies the State
21 Board of Education prior to October 15 of the applicable school
22 year, and meets the requirements established by the State Board of
23 Education pursuant to subsection H of this section.
